'''Ben Fayot''' (born 25 June 1937 in [[Luxembourg City]]) is a [[Luxembourg]]ish [[politician]] from the [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP). Fayot sat in the [[Chamber of Deputies of Luxembourg|Chamber of Deputies]] for five years from 1984. He was a [[Member of the European Parliament]]<ref name=eura>{{cite web
|url=http://www.europarl.europa.eu/members/archive/alphaOrder/view.do?language=EN&id=1154
|title=Your MEPs : Ben FAYOT
|work=[[Europa (web portal)|Europa]]|publisher=[[European Parliament]]|accessdate=5 April 2011}}</ref> from 1989 until 1999, when he returned to the Chamber of Deputies. Since 2004, he has been the president of the LSAP's deputation in the Chamber of Deputies.

By profession, Fayot was a political historian, specialising in the history of [[socialism]] in Luxembourg. He is also a contributor to the [[daily newspaper|daily]] ''[[Tageblatt]]'' newspaper on the topics related to socialism.
