{{Notability|1=bio|date=December 2010}} {{Nihongo|'''Kyouichi Tachikawa'''|立川 京一|Tachikawa Kyōichi|born 1966}} is a [[Japan]]ese historian specializing in international politics military history, specifically [[French Indochina]]. He was born in the [[Tokyo]]. He is a graduate of the [[Sophia University]] foreign language department. As of 1999, he lectures part-time at Sophia University and at [[Caritas Junior College]]. Currently he is working as a researcher for the [[Ministry of Defense (Japan)|Japanese Ministry of Defense]] where he does research on [[military history]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nids.go.jp/research/profile/senshi/03-tachikawa.html|title=研究者紹介 (Tatsukawa Kiyouiti:Researcher)|publisher=The National Institute for Defense Studies|language=Japanese|accessdate=31 December 2010|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206113031/http://www.nids.go.jp/research/profile/senshi/03-tachikawa.html|archivedate=6 December 2010|df=}}</ref>
