The following Egyptian pilots are confirmed or alleged to have become [[flying ace]]s by scoring five or more air-to-air victories while flying combat&mdash;mainly against the [[Israeli Air Force]]:
* Ali Wajai (alias Ali Wagedy) flew a [[MiG 21]] with 5 confirmed aerial victories.<ref>Air Aces Egypt http://aces.safarikovi.org/victories/egypt-middle.html Retrieved November 2017</ref> * [[Major]] Sami Marei was credited with five aerial victories between 1966 and 1968 while flying a MiG 21.<ref>Air Aces Egypt http://aces.safarikovi.org/victories/egypt-middle.html Retrieved November 2017</ref> Major Marei was [[killed in action]] on 26 February 1970. * [[Captain (OF-2)|Captain]] Samir Aziz Mikhail of the [[104th Air Brigade]] was credited with five aerial victories while flying a MiG 21. * Hussein Samy gained five aerial victories in a MiG 21.<ref>Air Combat Information Group http://www.acig.org/artman/publish/article_266.shtml Retrieved 23 December 2012.</ref><ref>[http://jpgleize.perso.neuf.fr/aces/isregy.htm Egyptian victory credits of the Arab-Israeli wars]</ref>
It is not known if this list is complete.
